        return 1

        return 0

sector = np.unique(data['鄉鎮市區'].tolist())
group = data.groupby('鄉鎮市區')
for i in sector:
    plt.figure(figsize = (8,8))
    # 照行政區分群
    g = group.get_group(i)
    # 將資料以每月整合並取平均值
    time_g = g.groupby(pd.Grouper(freq='3d')).median()
    # 用插值法補齊缺失值：前後資料平均
    time_g['總價元(log)'] = time_g['總價元(log)'].interpolate(method='linear')
    plt.plot(time_g['總價元'])
    plt.title(i)
    plt.show()

自相關與偏自相關函數¶

自相關是序列和自己滯後量的簡單相關。如果序列顯著自相關，均值和序列之前的值（滯後量）可能對預測當前值有幫助。

偏自相關也會傳遞相似的信息但是它傳遞的是序列和它滯後量的純粹相關，排除了其他中間滯後量對相關的貢獻。

ADF Test & KPSS Test¶

ADF Test：原假設序列為不平穩，若統計量小於 1%、5%、10%，則有(99%，95，90%）的機率來拒絕原假設，而序列則平穩，反之則不平穩。

KPSS Test：原假設序列平穩，若統計量大於 1%、5%、10%，則有(99%，95，90%）的機率來接受原假設，而序列則平穩，反之則不平穩。

1：兩個測試都得出序列不穩定->不平穩

2：兩個測試都平穩->序列平穩

3：KPSS=平穩的，ADF=不平穩->趨勢平穩，刪除趨勢使序列嚴格平穩情況

4：KPSS=非平穩且ADF平穩->差分平穩，使用差分使序列平穩

from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, kpss
log_price = s1['總價元(log)']
dftest = kpss(log_price, 'ct') 
print("KPSS Test statistic = {:.3f}".format(dftest[0])) 
print("P-value = {:.3f}".format(dftest[1])) 
print("Critical values :") 
for k, v in dftest[3].items(): 
    print("\t{}: {}".format(k, v))
    
result = adfuller(log_price, autolag='AIC') 
print(f'ADF Statistic: {result[0]}') 
print(f'p-value: {result[1]}') 
for key, value in result[4].items(): 
    print('Critial Values:') 
    print(f' {key}, {value}')

白噪音檢測¶

如平穩序列，白噪音也不是時間的函數，它的均值和方差並不隨時間變化。但是它與平穩序列的差異在於，白噪音完全隨機，均值為0。 從數學上來看，均值為0的完全隨機的數字序列是白噪音。

p < 0.05，拒絕原假設，序列為平穩且非白噪音

In [49]:

白噪聲檢測結果 p值: 1.2258087221077352e-05

def xgb_predict(train, val):
    train = np.array(train)
    x, y = train[:, :-1], train[:, -1]
    model = XGBRegressor(n_estimators = 1000)
    model.fit(x, y)
    
    val = np.array(val).reshape(1, -1)
    pred = model.predict(val)
    return pred[0]

Walk-forward validation¶

不斷加入預測過的test data進入train data

In [93]:
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error

def validate(train, test):
    predictions = []
    
    history = [x for x in train]
    
    for i in range(len(test)):
        test_x, test_y = test[i, :-1], test[:, -1]
        
        pred = xgb_predict(history, test_x[0])
        predictions.append(pred)
        
        history.append(test[i])
    error = mean_squared_error(test[:, -1], predictions, squared = False)
    
    return error, test[:, -1], predictions

def buildTrain(t, pastDay = 7, futureDay = 7):
    X_train, Y_train = [], []
    for i in range(t.shape[0]-futureDay-pastDay):
        X_train.append(np.array(t.iloc[i:i+pastDay]))
        Y_train.append(np.array(t.iloc[i+pastDay:i+pastDay+futureDay]))
    return np.array(X_train), np.array(Y_train)

price = log_price['總價元(log)']

X_train, Y_train = buildTrain(train)
X_test, Y_test = buildTrain(test)
X_train = X_train[:, :, np.newaxis]

from keras import backend as K
def root_mean_squared_error(y_true, y_pred):
        return K.sqrt(K.mean(K.square(y_pred - y_true)))
def buildManyToManyModel(shape):
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(LSTM(50, input_length=shape[1], input_dim=shape[2], return_sequences=True))
    model.add(LSTM(25, input_length=shape[1], input_dim=shape[2], return_sequences=True, dropout=0.3, recurrent_dropout=0.3))
    # output shape: (5, 1)
    model.add(TimeDistributed(Dense(1)))
    opt = Adam(learning_rate=0.003)
    model.compile(loss=root_mean_squared_error, optimizer="adam")
    model.summary()
    return model
